        {
            "_id": "wW41T2Rqe1HsYWiK",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/actions/Passive.webp",
            "name": "Repair Mode",
            "sort": 300000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "passive"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": null
                },
                "category": "defensive",
                "deathNote": true,
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>When the adamantine golem is at 0 HP, it isn't destroyed. Instead, it enters repair mode, during which it is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Slowed]{Slowed 1}, can't take reactions, and can take only the Self-Repair action.</p>\n<p>Once it has more than 30 HP, it can use any type of action and can use reactions, though it remains slowed 1 and can't take any reactions until the start of its next turn.</p>\n<p>If a critical hit with an adamantine <em>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.equipment-srd.Item.Vorpal]</em> weapon reduces the golem to 0 HP, or if such a weapon hits it while it's already at 0 HP, then the golem is destroyed.</p>"
                },
                "publication": {
                    "license": "OGL",
                    "remaster": false,
                    "title": ""
                },
                "rules": [],
                "slug": null,
                "traits": {
                    "rarity": "common",
                    "value": []
                }
            },
            "type": "action"
        },
        {
            "_id": "GliiYsgCIg3rdZ5a",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/actions/Passive.webp",
            "name": "Vulnerable to Dispelling",
            "sort": 400000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "passive"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": null
                },
                "category": "defensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>The golem can be targeted by @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.Disjunction] and @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.Dispel Magic].</p>\n<p>If targeted by such a spell of 9th rank or higher, the golem has its resistance to physical damage lowered to 15 and is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Slowed]{Slowed 1} (or @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Slowed]{Slowed 2} if in repair mode) for [[/gmr 1d4 #rounds]]{1d4 rounds}. During this time, if the golem is reduced to 0 HP while already in repair mode, it is destroyed.</p>"
                },
                "publication": {
                    "license": "OGL",
                    "remaster": false,
                    "title": ""
                },
